      <abstract>
        <variablelist>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHAT?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                Virtual machines can directly access host PCI or USB devices.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>WHY?</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                A virtual machine that is assigned direct access to a host device can use all its
                capabilities.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>GOAL</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                After completing the included procedures, you will be able to assign a host PCI or
                USB device to a virtual machine using both the graphical application &vmm; and the
                command-line tool &virsh;.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>EFFORT</term>
            <listitem>
              <para>
                It takes less than 30 minutes to understand and manage assigning a host device to a
                virtual machine.
              </para>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
          <varlistentry>
            <term>REQUIREMENTS</term>
            <listitem>
              <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    A &libvirt;-based &vmhost; running at least one virtual machine
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    <package>libvirt-client</package> and <package>virt-manager</package> packages
                    installed on the host
                  </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                  <para>
                    &rootuser; privileges
                  </para>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
          </varlistentry>
        </variablelist>
